article.description: — Tyon Grant-Foster had 27 points in Grand Canyon's 96-75 win over Southern Utah on Thursday night.
article.headline: Grant-Foster's 27 lead Grand Canyon past Southern Utah 96-75
article.linkText: Grant-Foster's 27 lead Grand Canyon past Southern Utah 96-75
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- — Tyon Grant-Foster had 27 points in Grand Canyon's 96-75 win over Southern Utah on Thursday night. Grant-Foster added five rebounds for the Antelopes (13-1, 3-0 Western Athletic Conference). Gabe McGlothan added 18 points while going 8 of 10 from the field, and he also had 10 rebounds. Collin Moore was 4 of 7 shooting, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 6 for 6 from the line to finish with 15 points, while adding five steals. It was the 10th straight victory for the Antelopes. The Thunderbirds (5-9, 0-3) were led in scoring by Parsa Fallah, who finished with 24 points, seven rebounds and two steals. Braden Housley added 15 points and eight rebounds for Southern Utah. In addition, Dominique Ford had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
